Class MyResBundle

  • java.lang.Object
    • MyResBundle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class MyResBundle
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This is my own implementation of the essential features of a text-oriented Resource Bundle. It is needed because the standard Java ResourceBundle class does not read French special characters when encoded in UTF-8, and it does not seem to read regular English keys when encoded in UTF-16.

    MyResBundle reads a *.properties file (UTF-8) with normal file readers and stores the lookup table in a TreeMap. Its getString() method returns the value for any key, or an error message if the key is not found.

    getBundle gives error messages in English because we can't load the lookUpTable for any other language.
